The paper is about neural architecture search (NAS) and the creation of a public dataset for NAS research. The dataset is focused on convolutional architectures and evaluated on CIFAR-10, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves optimization algorithms and the use of computational resources, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
